[Event "Baker Bridge - Negative Doubles and Cue-Bid Support"]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "2"]
[Dealer "N"]
[Vulnerable "NS"]
[Deal "N:AT532.AJT.987.A8 Q74.K54.Q54.J632 K9.862.AK63.KQ75 J86.Q973.JT2.T94"]
[Declarer "N"]
[Contract "3NT"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "N"]
1S 2H X pass 2NT pass 3NT pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 2, chOption: N, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:0, nBasis: 2, nRot: 2, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "6cac296dc73fe834aaec432e999378531ac07c3d73c29eea7d5169999db6f6cd"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/negative_doubles"]
[Student "S"]
{SOUTH has 15 points, and when East overcalls 2\H in front 
of her she has a perfect Negative Double - showing both of the Minor suits.

NORTH doesn't like the Minor suits, but he has stoppers in \Hs, so 
he bids 2NT.

SOUTH is more than happy to raise to 3NT.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "4"]
[Dealer "E"]
[Vulnerable "All"]
[Deal "E:9.KQJ7.AK6.AQT54 AQJ73.T3.Q932.73 T86.A9642.84.K62 K542.85.JT75.J98"]
[Declarer "E"]
[Contract "4H"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "E"]
1C 1S X pass 4H pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 4, chOption: E, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 0, nRot: 1, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "418495dc73f85ae1b5a49d6f38bab3744a08906625a044f4bc8177cd1cc35837"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/negative_doubles"]
[Student "S"]
{WEST would have responded 1\H if SOUTH had not overcalled. 
But with only 8 points he cannot bid at the 2-level. The Negative Double solves his problem, 
giving this information to partner.

EAST has good \Hs and enough points to bid game. 
Notice that if SOUTH had remained silent, WEST would have responded 1\H, 
and EAST would have jumped to game.}

